HEADWORD: Dakota group
<hw>Da*ko"ta group`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A
subdivision at the base of the cretaceous formation in Western North
America; -- so named from the region where the strata were first
studied.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

